spanGrp.span: ‘I saw something like a peccary that played with a cat.
Í sũã'-je rö sirak kepi je nẽ jinõ-gẽ michi ra
The cat pulled its tail up and down inside a huge house.
Michi të í mẽlek sige-gẽ jishögö mẽ jamĩnã dianã jũ tã'ĩ kate jãrga
There lived just the two of them. It seems that they lived inside the house;
jie-wa b-ol kela bö sẽr jalali Jie-wa ser-gẽ jũ jãrga juela bi
it seems that they advised each other.
Then the cat thought about trying to devour a bird.
Michi të í sh/ (_) begetsá-nã mãĩ dú kel í mĩ jega í kötö-pa
The cat went off showing its hand up and down in front of the bird.
Ñerö michi mẽnẽu-mĩ jula kashö-gẽ jamĩnã dianã í wö nã
Then it seems that the bird flew away from him;
Juela kepi mẽ/ dú junã'u-mĩ í yiga
so he could not reach him with his hand.
ka í jula denẽ ĩã dú gugö
Then the critter came down the roof and went through where the water flows down and is collected;
Ñerö mãĩ plötöbö datse je jũktö mẽ wagweta jẽk jẽk pakká-ka diglö watsõ-glö jãr jeska
but he got pressed in there. Then the critter’s hand burst bang!
í wö tenã'-wã Jeska í (_) plötöbö konã' ¡pá í jula
Meanwhile it went to a flat surface and nothing could be seen.
Batamẽ í desãu kã' kẽi inga Je ra ka jirö juenã ĩã
So, he covered his face; he went to see if he could eat something from the litter.
Ñerö í wö pagögá-wã í mẽnẽu jirö ñõ-pa kãbroi nã
He remembered the bird and left.
Í jẽr jãnã' ĩã í dú me í mẽnẽu-mĩ
But the bird was not there; the house was empty.
Ka dú juenã í jũ kel wakbö
